The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Bhopal, Aug. 30 (PTI): The Madhya Pradesh government has decided to confer the official title of Rashtra Rishis on all teachers at state-run schools.           
	This has offended minority leaders who questioned the logic behind calling teachers rishis, a term associated with Hindu sages. The state had recently asked students to perform the surya namaskar.                  
	 Kathmandu (PTI): A Pakistani has been arrested at Nepals international airport for illegal possession of Rs 23 lakh in Indian currency. Abdul Karim was held during a security check after he arrived from Qatar on Saturday. The notes were in Rs 500 denomination. It is illegal to carry Indian rupees of 500 and 1,000 denomination in Nepal.                   
	 Chandigarh (PTI): A helicopter ferrying Punjab deputy chief minister Sukhbir Singh Badal from Delhi made an emergency landing in Chandigarh on Sunday following a suspected technical fault. The helicopter landed about 500 yards from the BSF helipad where it was supposed to land. No one was hurt, an official said.                   
	 Bahraich (PTI): A Nepalese allegedly running a cross-border fake Indian currency racket has been arrested near the India-Nepal border in Bahraich in Uttar Pradesh. Vikki Manihar was arrested with fake Rs 500 notes.                   
	 Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): A 28-year-old man suspected to have links with extremists in Kerala and outside was taken into custody just before he was about to leave for Kuwait. The Intelligence Bureau had alerted airports about Kabeer Koyambathudi.                  
	 Ahmedabad (PIT): Over 13 naphtha-filled containers of a goods train caught fire after one of the containers derailed near a village in Gujarats Kutch district on Sunday evening. There were no casualties, police said. Fire fighters detached 12 containers to avoid further damage.                                                                                                                           
